 # ===== Azure OpenAI Configuration =====
# Copy these settings to your .env.local file

# Your Azure OpenAI API Key
AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=YOUR_AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY_HERE

# Alternative naming (for compatibility)
AZURE_OPENAI_KEY_1=YOUR_AZURE_OPENAI_BACKUP_KEY_HERE

# Azure OpenAI Endpoint
AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=https://neuroflow-hub.openai.azure.com/

# API Version (stable working version)
AZURE_OPENAI_API_VERSION=2024-04-01-preview

# Deployment Names (what works in your Azure)
AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT=gpt-4.1
DEPLOYMENT_NAME=gpt-4.1

# For DALL-E 3
AZURE_DEPLOYMENT_NAME=dall-e-3

# ===== Status =====
# ✅ gpt-4.1 - Working
# ✅ dall-e-3 - Working  
# ❌ gpt-4 - Not deployed in your Azure
# ❌ gpt-35-turbo - Not deployed in your Azure

# ===== Instructions =====
# 1. Create/edit .env.local file in your project root
# 2. Copy the lines above to .env.local
# 3. Restart your development server: npm run dev
# 4. Test in your app - Azure OpenAI should work now! 